Setting Rpi to do print jobs and provide feedback using python

Install Required Software

sudo apt-get install python3 python3-pip

AWS IoT SDK for Python:

pip3 install AWSIoTPythonSDK

Install CUPS to manage printers:

sudo apt-get install cups

sudo usermod -aG lpadmin pi # Add the default 'pi' user to the lpadmin group

Install Boto3 to interact with AWS services:

pip3 install boto3

AWS Credentials and IoT Configuration

AWS CLI:

pip3 install awscli

aws configure

Follow the prompts to enter your AWS Access Key, Secret Key, and default region.

Ensure the local directory for downloading files from S3 exists:

mkdir -p /home/veris/Desktop/Printer/temp

Write the python script which will do the following jobs:

· Download file from S3 and store it locally

· Print the downloaded file

· Delete the file from local storage and S3

· Post the list of active printers to AWS IoT core

· Post PrintJob log to AWS IoT Core

Put the code to run on boot:

Crontab –e

@reboot (sleep 15; /usr/bin/python3 /home/veris/desktop/Printer/final/final.py)

“Ctrl + O”

“Press Enter”

“Ctrl + x”
